#. desklet.js:33 quotes.js:13
msgid ""
"The impediment to action advances action. What stands in the way becomes the "
"way."
msgstr ""
"El obstáculo que impide actuar impulsa la acción. Lo que se interpone en el "
"camino se convierte en el camino."

#. desklet.js:34 quotes.js:14 quotes.js:17 quotes.js:20 quotes.js:23
#. quotes.js:26 quotes.js:29 quotes.js:32 quotes.js:35 quotes.js:38
#. quotes.js:41 quotes.js:44 quotes.js:47 quotes.js:50 quotes.js:53
#. quotes.js:56 quotes.js:59 quotes.js:62 quotes.js:203 quotes.js:206
#. quotes.js:209 quotes.js:212 quotes.js:215 quotes.js:218 quotes.js:221
#. quotes.js:224 quotes.js:326 quotes.js:329 quotes.js:332 quotes.js:335
#. quotes.js:338 quotes.js:341 quotes.js:344
msgid "Marcus Aurelius"
msgstr "Marco Aurelio"

#. desklet.js:35 quotes.js:15 quotes.js:225
msgid "Meditations, Book 5"
msgstr "Meditaciones, Libro 5"

#. desklet.js:161
msgid "Unknown"
msgstr "Desconocido"

#. quotes.js:16
msgid "Waste no more time arguing about what a good man should be. Be one."
msgstr ""
"No pierdas más tiempo discutiendo sobre cómo debe ser un buen hombre. Sé uno."

#. quotes.js:18 quotes.js:333
msgid "Meditations, Book 10"
msgstr "Meditaciones, Libro 10"

#. quotes.js:19
msgid "If it is not right, do not do it; if it is not true, do not say it."
msgstr "Si no está bien, no lo hagas; si no es verdad, no lo digas."

#. quotes.js:21 quotes.js:51 quotes.js:213 quotes.js:345
msgid "Meditations, Book 12"
msgstr "Meditaciones, Libro XII"

#. quotes.js:22
msgid "The best revenge is not to be like your enemy."
msgstr "La mejor venganza es no ser como tu enemigo."

#. quotes.js:24 quotes.js:45 quotes.js:48 quotes.js:216
msgid "Meditations, Book 6"
msgstr "Meditaciones, Libro 6"

#. quotes.js:25
msgid "Loss is nothing else but change, and change is Nature's delight."
msgstr ""
"La pérdida no es más que un cambio, y el cambio es el deleite de la "
"naturaleza."

#. quotes.js:27
msgid "Meditations, Book 9"
msgstr "Meditaciones, Libro 9"

#. quotes.js:28
msgid ""
"How much more grievous are the consequences of anger than the causes of it."
msgstr "Las consecuencias de la ira son mucho más graves que sus causas."

#. quotes.js:30
msgid "Meditations, Book 11"
msgstr "Meditaciones, Libro 11"

#. quotes.js:31
msgid ""
"Never esteem anything as of advantage to you that will make you break your "
"word or lose your self-respect."
msgstr ""
"Nunca consideres una ventaja para ti aquello que te haga incumplir tu "
"palabra o perder tu dignidad."

#. quotes.js:33
msgid "Meditations, Book 3"
msgstr "Meditaciones, Libro 3"

#. quotes.js:34
msgid ""
"Do every act of your life as though it were the very last act of your life."
msgstr "Haz cada cosa en tu vida como si fuera la última que fueras a hacer."

#. quotes.js:36 quotes.js:57
msgid "Meditations, Book 2"
msgstr "Meditaciones, Libro 2"

#. quotes.js:37
msgid ""
"You have power over your mind, not outside events. Realize this, and you "
"will find strength."
msgstr ""
"Tienes control sobre tu mente, no sobre los acontecimientos externos. Date "
"cuenta de ello y encontrarás la fuerza."

#. quotes.js:39 quotes.js:54 quotes.js:204 quotes.js:327 quotes.js:330
#. quotes.js:336 quotes.js:339 quotes.js:342
msgid "Meditations, Book 4"
msgstr "Meditaciones, Libro 4"

#. quotes.js:40
msgid ""
"Very little is needed to make a happy life; it is all within yourself, in "
"your way of thinking."
msgstr ""
"Se necesita muy poco para ser feliz; todo está en ti mismo, en tu forma de "
"pensar."

#. quotes.js:42 quotes.js:60 quotes.js:63 quotes.js:207 quotes.js:210
#. quotes.js:219 quotes.js:222
msgid "Meditations, Book 7"
msgstr "Meditaciones, Libro 7"

#. quotes.js:43
msgid ""
"Accept the things to which fate binds you, and love the people with whom "
"fate brings you together."
msgstr ""
"Acepta lo que el destino te depara y ama a las personas con las que el "
"destino te une."

#. quotes.js:46
msgid ""
"The object of life is not to be on the side of the majority, but to escape "
"finding oneself in the ranks of the insane."
msgstr ""
"El objetivo de la vida no es estar del lado de la mayoría, sino evitar "
"acabar entre las filas de los locos."

#. quotes.js:49
msgid ""
"It is not death that a man should fear, but he should fear never beginning "
"to live."
msgstr ""
"No es la muerte lo que el hombre debe temer, sino no llegar a empezar a "
"vivir."

#. quotes.js:52
msgid "The happiness of your life depends upon the quality of your thoughts."
msgstr "La felicidad de tu vida depende de la calidad de tus pensamientos."

#. quotes.js:55
msgid ""
"When you wake up in the morning, tell yourself: the people I deal with today "
"will be meddling, ungrateful, arrogant, dishonest, jealous and surly. They "
"are like this because they cannot tell good from evil. But I have seen the "
"beauty of good, and the ugliness of evil, and have recognized that the "
"wrongdoer has a nature related to my own."
msgstr ""
"Cuando te levantes por la mañana, repítete a ti mismo: Las personas con las "
"que trataré hoy serán entrometidas, desagradecidas, arrogantes, deshonestas, "
"envidiosas y hoscas. Son así porque no saben distinguir el bien del mal. "
"Pero yo he visto la belleza del bien y la fealdad del mal, y he comprendido "
"que quien hace el mal tiene una naturaleza parecida a la mía."

#. quotes.js:58
msgid ""
"Look back over the past, with its changing empires that rose and fell, and "
"you can foresee the future too. Its pattern will be the same, deviating only "
"in minor details. And to watch the mortal life of one man is to see them all."
msgstr ""
"Si echamos la vista atrás al pasado, con sus imperios cambiantes que "
"surgieron y cayeron, también podemos vislumbrar el futuro. Su patrón será el "
"mismo, con solo algunas pequeñas diferencias. Y observar la vida mortal de "
"un solo hombre es como verlas a todas."

#. quotes.js:61
msgid ""
"Almost nothing material is needed for a happy life, for he who has "
"understood existence."
msgstr ""
"Quien ha comprendido el sentido de la vida no necesita casi nada material "
"para ser feliz."

#. quotes.js:64
msgid ""
"Make the best use of what is in your power, and take the rest as it happens."
msgstr ""
"Aprovecha al máximo lo que está en tus manos y deja que el resto siga su "
"curso."

#. quotes.js:65 quotes.js:68 quotes.js:71 quotes.js:74 quotes.js:77
#. quotes.js:80 quotes.js:83 quotes.js:86 quotes.js:89 quotes.js:92
#. quotes.js:95 quotes.js:98 quotes.js:101 quotes.js:104 quotes.js:107
#. quotes.js:110 quotes.js:227 quotes.js:230 quotes.js:233 quotes.js:236
#. quotes.js:239 quotes.js:242 quotes.js:245 quotes.js:347 quotes.js:350
#. quotes.js:353 quotes.js:356
msgid "Epictetus"
msgstr "Epicteto"

#. quotes.js:66
msgid "Enchiridion, I"
msgstr "Enquiridion, I"

#. quotes.js:67
msgid "No man is free who is not master of himself."
msgstr "Nadie es libre si no es dueño de sí mismo."

#. quotes.js:69 quotes.js:231
msgid "Discourses, 2.1"
msgstr "Discursos, 2.1"

#. quotes.js:70
msgid ""
"First say to yourself what you would be; and then do what you have to do."
msgstr ""
"Primero, pregúntate a ti mismo qué quieres ser; y luego haz lo que tengas "
"que hacer."

#. quotes.js:72
msgid "Discourses, 3.23"
msgstr "Discursos, 3.23"

#. quotes.js:73
msgid ""
"If you want to improve, be content to be thought foolish and stupid with "
"regard to external things."
msgstr ""
"Si quieres mejorar, no te importe que te tomen por tonto o estúpido en lo "
"que respecta a las cosas externas."

#. quotes.js:75
msgid "Enchiridion, XIII"
msgstr "Enquiridion, XIII"

#. quotes.js:76
msgid ""
"Freedom is not procured by a full enjoyment of what is desired, but by "
"controlling the desire."
msgstr ""
"La libertad no se consigue disfrutando plenamente de lo que se desea, sino "
"controlando el deseo."

#. quotes.js:78
msgid "Discourses, 4.1"
msgstr "Discursos, 4.1"

#. quotes.js:79
msgid ""
"People are disturbed not by things, but by the views which they take of "
"things."
msgstr ""
"Lo que perturba a las personas no son las cosas en sí, sino la visión que "
"tienen de ellas."

#. quotes.js:81 quotes.js:348
msgid "Enchiridion, V"
msgstr "Enquiridion, V"

#. quotes.js:82
msgid "Seek not the good in external things; seek it in yourself."
msgstr "No busques lo bueno en las cosas externas; búscalo en ti mismo."

#. quotes.js:84
msgid "Discourses, 3.24"
msgstr "Discursos, 3.24"

#. quotes.js:85
msgid ""
"Never say about anything that I have lost it; but only that I have given it "
"back."
msgstr "Nunca digas de nada que lo he perdido, sino solo que lo he devuelto."

#. quotes.js:87
msgid "Enchiridion, XI"
msgstr "Enquiridion, XI"

#. quotes.js:88
msgid ""
"Seek not for the things which happen as you wish; but wish the things which "
"happen to be as they are, and you will have a tranquil life."
msgstr ""
"No busques que las cosas sucedan como tú deseas; más bien, desea que las "
"cosas sucedan tal y como son, y tendrás una vida tranquila."

#. quotes.js:90
msgid "Enchiridion, VIII"
msgstr "Enquiridion, VIII"

#. quotes.js:91
msgid ""
"Wealth consists not in having great possessions, but in having few wants."
msgstr ""
"La riqueza no consiste en tener muchas posesiones, sino en tener pocas "
"necesidades."

#. quotes.js:93 quotes.js:96 quotes.js:99 quotes.js:108 quotes.js:111
msgid "Discourses"
msgstr "Discursos"

#. quotes.js:94
msgid ""
"He is a wise man who does not grieve for the things which he has not, but "
"rejoices for those which he has."
msgstr ""
"Es sabio aquel que no se lamenta por lo que no tiene, sino que se alegra por "
"lo que sí tiene."

#. quotes.js:97
msgid "Don't explain your philosophy. Embody it."
msgstr "No expliques tu filosofía. Vívela."

#. quotes.js:100
msgid ""
"We cannot choose our external circumstances, but we can always choose how we "
"respond to them."
msgstr ""
"No podemos elegir las circunstancias externas, pero siempre podemos elegir "
"cómo reaccionar ante ellas."

#. quotes.js:102
msgid "Enchiridion"
msgstr "Enquiridion"

#. quotes.js:103
msgid "First learn the meaning of what you say, and then speak."
msgstr "Primero, piensa bien lo que vas a decir y luego habla."

#. quotes.js:105
msgid "Discourses, 1.17"
msgstr "Discursos, 1.17"

#. quotes.js:106
msgid ""
"You become what you give your attention to. If you yourself don't choose "
"what thoughts and images you expose yourself to, someone else will."
msgstr ""
"Te conviertes en aquello a lo que prestas atención. Si tú mismo no eliges a "
"qué pensamientos e imágenes te expones, lo hará otra persona."

#. quotes.js:109
msgid ""
"There is only one way to happiness and that is to cease worrying about "
"things which are beyond the power of our will."
msgstr ""
"Solo hay un camino hacia la felicidad, y es dejar de preocuparse por cosas "
"que escapan a nuestro control."

#. quotes.js:112
msgid "All things are foreign to us; time alone is ours."
msgstr "Todo nos resulta ajeno; solo el tiempo nos pertenece."

#. quotes.js:113 quotes.js:116 quotes.js:119 quotes.js:122 quotes.js:125
#. quotes.js:128 quotes.js:131 quotes.js:134 quotes.js:137 quotes.js:140
#. quotes.js:143 quotes.js:146 quotes.js:149 quotes.js:152 quotes.js:248
#. quotes.js:251 quotes.js:254 quotes.js:257 quotes.js:260 quotes.js:263
#. quotes.js:266 quotes.js:269 quotes.js:359 quotes.js:362 quotes.js:365
#. quotes.js:368 quotes.js:371 quotes.js:374
msgid "Seneca"
msgstr "Seneca"

#. quotes.js:114 quotes.js:117
msgid "Letters from a Stoic, I"
msgstr "Cartas de un estoico, I"

#. quotes.js:115
msgid "While we are postponing, life speeds by."
msgstr "Mientras lo posponemos, la vida pasa volando."

#. quotes.js:118
msgid ""
"It is not the man who has too little, but the man who craves more, that is "
"poor."
msgstr "No es pobre quien tiene muy poco, sino quien ansía tener más."

#. quotes.js:120 quotes.js:144
msgid "Letters from a Stoic, II"
msgstr "Cartas de un estoico, II"

#. quotes.js:121
msgid "Begin at once to live, and count each separate day as a separate life."
msgstr ""
"Empieza a vivir desde ahora mismo y considera cada día como una vida en sí "
"misma."

#. quotes.js:123 quotes.js:372
msgid "Letters from a Stoic, CI"
msgstr "Cartas de un estoico, CI"

#. quotes.js:124
msgid ""
"The greatest obstacle to living is expectancy, which hangs upon tomorrow and "
"loses today."
msgstr ""
"El mayor obstáculo para vivir es la expectación, que se aferra al mañana y "
"pierde el hoy."

#. quotes.js:126
msgid "On the Shortness of Life, IX"
msgstr "Sobre la brevedad de la vida, IX"

#. quotes.js:127
msgid "No man was ever wise by chance."
msgstr "Ningún hombre ha llegado a ser sabio por casualidad."

#. quotes.js:129 quotes.js:363
msgid "Letters from a Stoic, LXXVI"
msgstr "Cartas de un estoico, LXXVI"

#. quotes.js:130
msgid ""
"Retire into yourself as much as you can; associate with those who are likely "
"to improve you."
msgstr ""
"Retírate a tu interior tanto como puedas; rodéate de personas que puedan "
"ayudarte a mejorar."

#. quotes.js:132
msgid "Letters from a Stoic, VII"
msgstr "Cartas de un estoico, VII"

#. quotes.js:133
msgid "A happy life is one which is in accordance with its own nature."
msgstr ""
"Una vida feliz es aquella que está en armonía con su propia naturaleza."

#. quotes.js:135
msgid "On the Happy Life, III"
msgstr "Sobre la vida feliz, III"

#. quotes.js:136
msgid "If you wish to be loved, love."
msgstr "Si deseas ser amado, ama."

#. quotes.js:138
msgid "Letters from a Stoic, IX"
msgstr "Cartas de un estoico, IX"

#. quotes.js:139
msgid "We suffer more often in imagination than in reality."
msgstr "Sufrimos más a menudo en la imaginación que en la realidad."

#. quotes.js:141
msgid "Letters from a Stoic, XIII"
msgstr "Cartas de un estoico, XIII"

#. quotes.js:142
msgid "One who is everywhere is nowhere."
msgstr "Quien está en todas partes no está en ninguna."

#. quotes.js:145
msgid "To live is to fight."
msgstr "Vivir es luchar."

#. quotes.js:147
msgid "Letters from a Stoic, XCVI"
msgstr "Cartas de un estoico, XCVI"

#. quotes.js:148
msgid "Luck is what happens when preparation meets opportunity."
msgstr ""
"La suerte es lo que sucede cuando la preparación se encuentra con la "
"oportunidad."

#. quotes.js:150
msgid "Epistulae Morales"
msgstr "Epístolas morales"

#. quotes.js:151
msgid ""
"True happiness is to enjoy the present, without anxious dependence upon the "
"future, not to amuse ourselves with either hopes or fears but to rest "
"satisfied with what we have, which is sufficient."
msgstr ""
"La verdadera felicidad consiste en disfrutar del presente, sin depender con "
"ansiedad del futuro, sin dejarnos llevar ni por las esperanzas ni por los "
"temores, sino sintiéndonos satisfechos con lo que tenemos, que es suficiente."

#. quotes.js:153
msgid "Letters from a Stoic"
msgstr "Cartas de un estoico"

#. quotes.js:154
msgid "Better to trip with the feet than with the tongue."
msgstr "Más vale tropezar con los pies que con la lengua."

#. quotes.js:155 quotes.js:158 quotes.js:161 quotes.js:164 quotes.js:167
#. quotes.js:287 quotes.js:290
msgid "Zeno of Citium"
msgstr "Zenón de Citio"

#. quotes.js:156
msgid "Lives of the Eminent Philosophers, 7.26"
msgstr "Vidas de los filósofos ilustres, 7.26"

#. quotes.js:157
msgid "The goal of life is to live in agreement with Nature."
msgstr "El objetivo de la vida es vivir en armonía con la naturaleza."

#. quotes.js:159
msgid "Lives of the Eminent Philosophers, 7.87"
msgstr "Vidas de los filósofos ilustres, 7.87"

#. quotes.js:160
msgid ""
"We have two ears and one mouth, so that we should listen more than we say."
msgstr ""
"Tenemos dos oídos y una boca, para que escuchemos más de lo que hablamos."

#. quotes.js:162 quotes.js:165
msgid "Lives of the Eminent Philosophers"
msgstr "Vidas de los filósofos ilustres"

#. quotes.js:163
msgid "Man conquers the world by conquering himself."
msgstr "El hombre conquista el mundo al conquistarse a sí mismo."

#. quotes.js:166
msgid "All the good are friends of one another."
msgstr "Todos los buenos son amigos entre sí."

#. quotes.js:168
msgid "Lives of the Eminent Philosophers, 7.32"
msgstr "Vidas de los filósofos ilustres, 7.32"

#. quotes.js:169
msgid ""
"Lead me, Zeus, lead me, Destiny, wherever I have been assigned by you. I "
"will follow without hesitation; and if I am unwilling, because I am wicked, "
"I will follow nonetheless."
msgstr ""
"Guíame, Zeus, guíame, Destino, allá donde me hayáis destinado. Te seguiré "
"sin dudarlo; y si no estoy dispuesto a hacerlo, por ser malvado, te seguiré "
"de todos modos."

#. quotes.js:170 quotes.js:173 quotes.js:176 quotes.js:284
msgid "Cleanthes"
msgstr "Cleantes"

#. quotes.js:171 quotes.js:174
msgid "Hymn to Zeus"
msgstr "Himno a Zeus"

#. quotes.js:172
msgid ""
"All things are parts of one single system, which is called Nature; the "
"individual life is good when it is in harmony with Nature."
msgstr ""
"Todas las cosas forman parte de un único sistema, que se denomina "
"Naturaleza; la vida individual es buena cuando está en armonía con la "
"Naturaleza."

#. quotes.js:175
msgid "Practice yourself in little things, and thence proceed to greater."
msgstr ""
"Practica primero con cosas pequeñas y, a partir de ahí, pasa a las más "
"grandes."

#. quotes.js:177
msgid "Lives of the Eminent Philosophers, 7.168"
msgstr "Vidas de los filósofos ilustres, 7.168"

#. quotes.js:178
msgid ""
"If you accomplish something good with hard work, the labor passes quickly, "
"but the good endures; if you do something shameful in pursuit of pleasure, "
"the pleasure passes quickly, but the shame endures."
msgstr ""
"Si consigues algo bueno gracias al esfuerzo, el esfuerzo pasa rápido, pero "
"lo bueno perdura; si haces algo vergonzoso en busca del placer, el placer "
"pasa rápido, pero la vergüenza perdura."

#. quotes.js:179 quotes.js:182 quotes.js:185 quotes.js:188 quotes.js:191
#. quotes.js:272 quotes.js:275 quotes.js:278 quotes.js:281
msgid "Musonius Rufus"
msgstr "Musonio Rufo"

#. quotes.js:180 quotes.js:279
msgid "Lectures, VI"
msgstr "Conferencias, VI"

#. quotes.js:181
msgid ""
"We must not say that it befits only the philosopher to inquire how one ought "
"to live rightly; for philosophy is nothing else than this — the inquiry into "
"what is fitting and appropriate for a human being."
msgstr ""
"No debemos decir que solo corresponde al filósofo indagar cómo se debe vivir "
"correctamente; pues la filosofía no es otra cosa que esto: la indagación "
"sobre lo que es adecuado y apropiado para el ser humano."

#. quotes.js:183
msgid "Lectures, I"
msgstr "Conferencias, I"

#. quotes.js:184
msgid ""
"Choose to die well while you can; wait too long, and it might become "
"impossible to do so."
msgstr ""
"Elige morir bien mientras puedas; si esperas demasiado, puede que ya no sea "
"posible hacerlo."

#. quotes.js:186
msgid "Lectures, VIII"
msgstr "Conferencias, VIII"

#. quotes.js:187
msgid ""
"The man who is truly good and wise neither struggles with adversity nor "
"complains of his lot; rather, he takes heart from even the harshest of "
"conditions."
msgstr ""
"El hombre verdaderamente bueno y sabio no se deja abatir por la adversidad "
"ni se queja de su suerte; al contrario, saca fuerzas incluso de las "
"circunstancias más difíciles."

#. quotes.js:189
msgid "Lectures, X"
msgstr "Conferencias, X"

#. quotes.js:190
msgid ""
"The philosopher's aim is not to hear many lectures and then fall silent, but "
"to live by those already heard."
msgstr ""
"El objetivo del filósofo no es escuchar muchas conferencias para luego "
"quedarse callado, sino vivir según lo que ya ha escuchado."

#. quotes.js:192 quotes.js:273
msgid "Lectures"
msgstr "Conferencias"

#. quotes.js:193
msgid "If I had followed the multitude, I would not have studied philosophy."
msgstr "Si hubiera seguido a la mayoría, no habría estudiado filosofía."

#. quotes.js:194 quotes.js:197 quotes.js:200 quotes.js:377
msgid "Chrysippus"
msgstr "Crisippo"

#. quotes.js:195
msgid "Lives of the Eminent Philosophers, 7.183"
msgstr "Vidas de los filósofos ilustres, 7.183"

#. quotes.js:196
msgid ""
"The virtues are interconnected; whoever truly possesses one virtue possesses "
"them all."
msgstr ""
"Las virtudes están interrelacionadas; quien posee verdaderamente una virtud, "
"las posee todas."

#. quotes.js:198
msgid "Lives of the Eminent Philosophers, 7.125"
msgstr "Vidas de los filósofos ilustres, 7.125"

#. quotes.js:199
msgid "No one is born a sage; goodness is an art which must be learned."
msgstr "Nadie nace sabio; la bondad es un arte que hay que aprender."

#. quotes.js:201
msgid "Fragments"
msgstr "Fragmentos"

#. quotes.js:202
msgid "The universe is change; our life is what our thoughts make it."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:205
msgid ""
"Dwell on the beauty of life. Watch the stars, and see yourself running with "
"them."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:208
msgid "The art of living is more like wrestling than dancing."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:211
msgid ""
"Everything is but what your opinion makes it; and that opinion lies with "
"yourself."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:214
msgid "Adapt yourself to the things with which your lot has been cast."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:217
msgid "Confine yourself to the present."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:220
msgid ""
"Dig within. There lies the well-spring of good: ever dig, and it will ever "
"flow."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:223
msgid ""
"Such as are thy habitual thoughts, such also will be the character of thy "
"mind."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:226
msgid "Difficulties are things that show a person what they are."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:228
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Discourses, 3.24"
msgid "Discourses, 1.24"
msgstr "Discursos, 3.24"

#. quotes.js:229
msgid "Only the educated are free."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:232
msgid "Know first who you are, and then adorn yourself accordingly."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:234
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Discourses, 2.1"
msgid "Discourses, 3.1"
msgstr "Discursos, 2.1"

#. quotes.js:235
msgid "If you wish to be a writer, write; if you wish to be a reader, read."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:237 quotes.js:354
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Discourses, 2.1"
msgid "Discourses, 2.18"
msgstr "Discursos, 2.1"

#. quotes.js:238
msgid ""
"When you close your doors and make darkness within, remember never to say "
"that you are alone, for you are not alone."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:240
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Discourses, 1.17"
msgid "Discourses, 1.14"
msgstr "Discursos, 1.17"

#. quotes.js:241
msgid "Lameness is an impediment to the leg, but not to the will."
